<h2>Finding Sublets</h2>
<p>Securing short-term housing for a summer internship in New York City requires proactive planning. Interns frequently seek flexible arrangements, typically from June through August [1sr4b9v/r/columbia].</p>

<p>University housing programs offer a structured option. NYU, for example, provides summer dorm offers and maintains a dedicated housing portal for Summer 2026 [1rnhw9x/r/nyu, 1qy2oeg/r/nyu]. Specific dorms, such as Lafayette and Broome, are recognized for their social environments [1okf4i0/r/nyu]. Columbia University also provides residential units for summer sublet, with some located within a five-minute walk to campus [1su5sn5/r/columbia]. Interns should be aware that university housing may impose guest restrictions [1r6r7ud/r/columbia].</p>

<p>Private sublets represent another prevalent choice. Many interns search for sublets in neighborhoods such as the East Village, West Village, SoHo, Kips Bay, and Midtown Manhattan [1tpjulo/r/nyu, 1tw2qav/r/nyu, 1sr4b9v/r/columbia]. Near Columbia, the Upper West Side and locations with convenient access to the 1, 2, or 3 subway lines are often preferred for easy transportation to Hudson Square or campus [1tnwaql/r/columbia, 1sx8io8/r/columbia, 1so8ars/r/columbia].</p>

<p>Budgeting is critical for summer housing in NYC. While Airbnb can be expensive [1rnhw9x/r/nyu], many interns target private rooms within shared apartments, with budgets ranging from approximately $1,450 to $2,000 per month [1tnwaql/r/columbia, 1qnukdt/r/nyu, 1sx8io8/r/columbia]. Some individuals seek private rooms with private baths [1qnukdt/r/nyu]. For those undertaking unpaid internships, financial aid for campus living may not be available, necessitating a focus on more affordable alternatives [1tk2fp9/r/nyu, 1sa0qn0/r/nyu]. High electricity bills during summer also constitute a significant expense to consider [1la3yi0/r/asknyc].</p>

<p>When searching for a sublet, evaluate amenities such as a dedicated desk, furnished space, and on-site laundry [1sx8io8/r/columbia, 1so8ars/r/columbia]. Some individuals prefer specific roommate demographics, for example, female-only apartmentmates [1tpjulo/r/nyu, 1su5sn5/r/columbia]. Always prioritize clear communication regarding move-in and move-out dates, as internship durations can vary, often spanning from early June to mid-August [1qnukdt/r/nyu, 1saxp7r/r/columbia].</p>
</InternWiki>
